title: tour: reference to Fibonacci sequence without explanation of what it is
body:
Context: http://127.0.0.1:3999/moretypes/23

So...utterly...lost.

The Fibonacci sequence is the sequence of numbers where the value(n) = value(n-1) + value (n-2) with the seed values value(0) = 0 and value(1) = 1. (source: http://nylira.com/a-tour-of-go-solutions/)

That's all I need.  I'll try to figure this out without looking up the actual solution.
